WEBVTT

00:01.167 --> 00:02.919
<i>Previously on</i> This Is Us...

00:03.003 --> 00:06.589
-Can I help you?
-Yeah, um, I'm looking
for a suit.

00:06.673 --> 00:08.675
Come on, Jack, just
say it like it is.

00:08.758 --> 00:10.010
We both know that
I wasn't there

00:10.093 --> 00:12.345
for Andy and Amber
like I should have been.

00:12.429 --> 00:15.390
You know, after your mother
and I split,

00:15.473 --> 00:18.184
I promised my best friend
and myself that

00:18.268 --> 00:21.021
I would fight to keep
you kids in my life.

00:21.104 --> 00:23.273
And for a long time, I tried.

00:23.356 --> 00:27.652
<i>In heartbreak, ten years</i>
<i>after her husband</i>

00:27.736 --> 00:29.446
<i>and my best friend died,</i>

00:29.529 --> 00:31.322
Rebecca and I found each other.

00:31.406 --> 00:33.408
Now, you don't have to be
happy for us,

00:33.491 --> 00:36.911
but we're not gonna apologize
for being together.

00:36.995 --> 00:39.873
Let's toast to your mother
not calling you William.

00:39.956 --> 00:41.207
<i>-Salud.</i>
<i>-Salud.</i>

01:00.560 --> 01:02.062
(laughter)

02:23.727 --> 02:25.729
♪ ♪

03:00.972 --> 03:02.390
<i>DOCTOR: I'd like to see</i>
<i>the blood pressure</i>

03:02.474 --> 03:03.808
<i>come down a little.</i>

03:03.892 --> 03:05.894
<i>-MIGUEL: Okay.</i>
<i>-How's the new hip treating you</i>

03:05.977 --> 03:07.604
<i>in the couple of months</i>
<i>since the wedding?</i>

03:07.687 --> 03:09.856
<i>MIGUEL:</i>
<i>Oh, the hip's great, thank you.</i>

03:09.939 --> 03:11.149
<i>DOCTOR: What about fatigue?</i>
<i>Now, you mentioned feeling</i>

03:11.232 --> 03:13.568
<i>shortness of breath</i>
<i>during exercise?</i>

03:13.651 --> 03:14.569
<i>MIGUEL:</i>
<i>Um...</i>

03:14.652 --> 03:16.363
I think I'd like to set you up

03:16.446 --> 03:17.447
for a stress test.

03:17.530 --> 03:19.991
I don't have time
for that, Doc, I'm sorry.

03:20.075 --> 03:22.535
You're not a young man
anymore, Mr. Rivas, no.

03:22.619 --> 03:24.829
<i>Our bodies don't recover</i>
<i>the way they used to.</i>

03:24.913 --> 03:26.206
<i>You've got to get some rest.</i>

03:26.289 --> 03:28.958
(Rebecca moans softly)

03:36.758 --> 03:39.552
Hey.

03:39.636 --> 03:42.222
Let's get you out of bed.

03:42.305 --> 03:44.516
(speaking indistinctly)

03:49.813 --> 03:53.650
Come on, let's get
your glasses on so you can see.

03:57.153 --> 03:59.155
Perfect.

04:00.407 --> 04:01.825
(Rebecca grunts)

04:04.327 --> 04:05.328
(Miguel speaking indistinctly)

04:05.412 --> 04:06.996
Mm-hmm.

04:11.960 --> 04:13.461
Bon appétit.

04:16.881 --> 04:20.677
All right, keep that tension
and raise it above your head.

04:20.760 --> 04:22.387
There you go, honey.

04:22.470 --> 04:24.764
-Keep the tension
on your shoulders. Perfect.
-(door opens)

04:24.848 --> 04:25.974
LAILA:
Hello?

04:26.057 --> 04:27.517
<i>-Hola.</i>
-Great, honey.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.185
Okay, lower it,
lower it back down...

04:29.269 --> 04:31.271
Good morning, Rebecca, Miguel.

04:31.354 --> 04:32.689
-Good morning, Laila.
-What's she...?

04:32.772 --> 04:34.733
-Wh-Who is that?
-Oh, that's Laila.

04:34.816 --> 04:36.651
She's our nurse.
She comes every...

04:36.735 --> 04:39.738
every day to help us out.
You know her.

04:39.821 --> 04:41.614
Okay.

04:41.698 --> 04:43.366
Of course. Yeah.

04:43.450 --> 04:45.869
Um, good morning, Laila.

04:45.952 --> 04:48.121
Can I help you
with your exercises?

04:48.204 --> 04:51.750
I-I think it's okay.
We've got it.

04:51.833 --> 04:53.376
-We're almost done here anyway.
-Mm-hmm.

04:53.460 --> 04:55.045
I'll go make sure
her meds are sorted.

04:55.128 --> 04:56.504
I already took care of that
as well.

04:56.588 --> 04:58.256
-Thank you.
-Okay.

04:58.340 --> 05:00.717
All right.
Want to try another one?

05:00.800 --> 05:02.802
-Mm-hmm.
-All right, let's pull that...

05:04.637 --> 05:09.309
See? I told you
we'd make it.

05:09.392 --> 05:11.644
From a little seed
to our first bloom.

05:11.728 --> 05:14.731
-Mm.
-One day at a time.

05:18.234 --> 05:20.820
One day at a time.

05:20.904 --> 05:22.781
That's right.

05:24.407 --> 05:26.534
<i>RANDALL (over phone):</i>
<i>So, how's Mom responding</i>
<i>to the new meds?</i>

05:26.618 --> 05:29.579
-(grunts)
-There we go. Okay.

05:29.662 --> 05:31.289
<i>KATE (over phone):</i>
<i>Jack and Hailey keep asking</i>
<i>to see Grandma and Grandpa.</i>

05:31.373 --> 05:32.999
<i>Can you Facetime?</i>

05:33.083 --> 05:34.292
<i>KEVIN (over phone):</i>
<i>Miguel, come on, man.</i>

05:34.376 --> 05:35.418
<i>I'm paying a lot of money</i>
<i>for this nurse.</i>

05:35.502 --> 05:37.128
<i>She comes highly recommended.</i>

05:37.212 --> 05:41.383
-One more each hand.
-Sun, mountain.

05:41.466 --> 05:42.967
Nice.

05:43.051 --> 05:44.928
She's, uh, she's adjusting,
Randall, yeah.

05:45.011 --> 05:47.722
Oh, uh, can we Facetime
tomorrow, Kate?

05:47.806 --> 05:49.432
I hear you, Kev, I hear you.

05:49.516 --> 05:50.558
<i>RANDALL:</i>
<i>I'll see you in a few weeks.</i>

05:50.642 --> 05:51.726
<i>KATE: Can't wait</i>
<i>for Thanksgiving.</i>

05:51.810 --> 05:52.894
<i>KEVIN:</i>
<i>See you in a couple days.</i>

05:52.977 --> 05:55.230
Okay, see you at Thanksgiving.
Take care.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.065
Earth.

05:59.275 --> 06:00.360
Sky.

06:00.443 --> 06:03.530
Nice.

06:03.613 --> 06:05.615
(snipping)

06:11.830 --> 06:14.040
(Risto whistles)

06:25.677 --> 06:27.679
(snipping resumes)

06:38.398 --> 06:39.816
<i>Mira.</i>

07:04.758 --> 07:08.136
<i>SPORTSCASTER:</i>
<i>Second-- two outs, two balls,</i>
<i>and two strikes.</i>

07:09.971 --> 07:11.139
<i>The pitch.</i>

07:11.222 --> 07:13.600
<i>-(bat hits ball)</i>
<i>-A little liner to right field.</i>

07:16.186 --> 07:17.979
-(chuckling): No, you...
<i>-Lo siento.</i>

07:18.063 --> 07:20.482
-I sorry.
-You must be Risto's boy.

07:21.524 --> 07:22.734
You a Pirates fan?

07:22.817 --> 07:24.819
(cheering on TV)

07:26.071 --> 07:27.614
Man, oh, man.

07:27.697 --> 07:30.450
Great player, that Clemente.
Great player.

07:30.533 --> 07:32.494
Can't understand a damn word
he says,

07:32.577 --> 07:34.454
but, uh, he sure is something.

07:37.874 --> 07:39.668
I got something for you.

07:39.751 --> 07:44.130
I caught a foul ball off
Mazeroski the other day.

07:46.466 --> 07:48.843
You been to a game yet?

07:48.927 --> 07:52.555
Well, tell your dad
he's got to take you.

07:52.639 --> 07:56.101
Forbes Field is... it's a gem.

07:56.184 --> 07:58.645
Try to sneak down to the seats
behind home plate.

07:58.728 --> 08:01.189
That's where I caught
that ball.

08:01.272 --> 08:03.775
Best seats in the house.

08:06.152 --> 08:09.197
Only want to see a game.

08:09.280 --> 08:13.451
No matter where to sit.

08:13.535 --> 08:16.705
Son, where you sit

08:16.788 --> 08:18.748
is all that matters.

08:22.585 --> 08:24.838
<i>SPORTSCASTER:</i>
<i>The relay. Safe!</i>

08:24.921 --> 08:27.632
(all cheer)

08:35.432 --> 08:39.936
America to call. To call.

08:40.020 --> 08:42.063
♪ <i>America's the greatest</i>
<i>land of all...</i> ♪

08:42.147 --> 08:45.775
America...

08:45.859 --> 08:49.487
the greatest land of all.

09:02.959 --> 09:05.211
Mike Rivers.

09:05.295 --> 09:07.172
Mike?

09:07.255 --> 09:09.382
I-I'm Mike Rivers.
That's me.

09:09.466 --> 09:11.634
Ah. Uh, Bill Lundy.

09:11.718 --> 09:13.595
-Hi. Nice to meet you.
-Pleasure to meet you.

09:13.678 --> 09:14.763
Uh, come on back.

09:14.846 --> 09:16.181
Okay.

09:18.141 --> 09:21.353
Well, Mike, your résumé
speaks for itself.

09:21.436 --> 09:24.022
Top salesman six straight
quarters

09:24.105 --> 09:25.857
-at John Fall's Men's Shop.
-Mm-hmm.

09:25.940 --> 09:27.776
You speak Spanish?

09:27.859 --> 09:31.821
Uh, I do, yes.

09:31.905 --> 09:33.865
Well, I won't pretend
that's not helpful.

09:33.948 --> 09:37.994
A lot of our new guys on site
barely speak a word of English.

09:38.078 --> 09:38.995
When can you start?

09:39.079 --> 09:41.664
I can start right away.

09:41.748 --> 09:43.792
-Thank you.
-Great.

09:43.875 --> 09:48.421
Um, the name's Miguel,
by the way.

09:48.505 --> 09:50.090
Miguel Rivas.

09:50.173 --> 09:51.925
I sent in two résumés,

09:52.008 --> 09:54.761
but, um, Miguel never got
a call back.

09:54.844 --> 09:57.389
Miguel. Okay.

09:57.472 --> 09:59.140
Am I saying it right?
Miguel?

09:59.224 --> 10:00.350
<i>Miguel.</i> But you can say

10:00.433 --> 10:02.227
whatever you want, Mr. Lundy.

10:02.310 --> 10:03.770
Um, Sally's just down the hall
that way.

10:03.853 --> 10:07.399
She'll get you situated
with your start paperwork...

10:07.482 --> 10:08.400
M-Miguel.

10:08.483 --> 10:09.567
Yes, that's perfect.

10:09.651 --> 10:11.277
-Thank you.
-All right.

10:16.658 --> 10:18.368
Merry Christmas. (laughs)

10:19.411 --> 10:22.163
Merry Christmas. Ah!

10:24.499 --> 10:26.501
Merry Christmas. Feliz Navidad.

10:26.584 --> 10:27.711
What'd you do to your hair?

10:29.254 --> 10:31.172
You don't like it?
Oh, by the way,

10:31.256 --> 10:34.467
I brought some, uh, wine.
It's, uh, good stuff.

10:34.551 --> 10:36.636
No wine. It's Christmas Eve,

10:36.720 --> 10:38.138
and we're having coquito.

10:40.890 --> 10:44.519
-It's good to see you, <i>mijo.</i>
-Good to see you, too, Papi.

10:44.602 --> 10:46.062
-You're always busy.
-Yeah, well...

10:46.146 --> 10:47.564
The new job treating you well?

10:47.647 --> 10:48.690
-Oh, I love it.
-Yeah?

10:48.773 --> 10:49.816
Yeah, uh, it's very challenging,

10:49.899 --> 10:52.444
but it also pays very well.

10:52.527 --> 10:54.738
I just got a new car.
A Chevy El Camino.

10:54.821 --> 10:55.905
What do I tell you
about saving?

11:02.370 --> 11:05.498
I know, Papi, I know.

11:05.582 --> 11:07.042
Come on, Papi,
you know how it is.

11:07.125 --> 11:08.460
I-I got to project success now.

11:08.543 --> 11:11.004
Well, how it is sure isn't
how it used to be.

11:11.087 --> 11:13.298
-I will toast to that. <i>Salud.</i>
<i>-Salud.</i>

11:14.758 --> 11:18.803
-Gabi's busy making pasteles,
but she says Merry Christmas.
-Mm.

11:18.887 --> 11:20.847
She also says she misses
your curly hair.

11:20.930 --> 11:22.724
Well, I'm not trying to look
like I just flew in

11:22.807 --> 11:24.684
from San Juan, Mami.

11:24.768 --> 11:26.728
(man singing in Spanish
on radio)

11:26.811 --> 11:28.063
How is she doing, by the way?

11:28.146 --> 11:31.566
-Take it day by day.
-Mm.

11:31.649 --> 11:34.319
You know, Mami,
I really wish that you would

11:34.402 --> 11:37.781
let me hire somebody to help you
take care of Aunt Gabi.

11:37.864 --> 11:39.657
She's got me.
Save your money.

11:39.741 --> 11:41.409
Mami, I have plenty of money.
Don't worry about it.

11:41.493 --> 11:42.327
Just let me help you.

11:47.082 --> 11:49.250
-You have something
to say, Papi?
-To who?

11:49.334 --> 11:51.169
You?

11:51.252 --> 11:54.047
The guy with the slick hair,
the slick car...

11:56.257 --> 11:58.718
What are you talking about?

12:01.638 --> 12:03.139
<i>Que no...</i>

12:16.277 --> 12:18.905
You-you split me in half
when you moved us here,

12:18.988 --> 12:20.782
and now I'm finally
figuring out, and what,

12:20.865 --> 12:22.867
you want me to struggle
like you?

12:25.036 --> 12:26.454
Why is it so hard for you
to watch me

12:26.538 --> 12:28.665
make something of myself
in this place?

12:28.748 --> 12:30.583
In this place that
you brought us to?

12:47.767 --> 12:50.645
I will.

12:50.729 --> 12:53.189
Enjoy the wine, Mami.

12:53.273 --> 12:54.482
I'm gonna go.

12:55.900 --> 12:58.820
I'm gonna go.
Merry Christmas.

13:08.329 --> 13:11.249
♪ <i>Rocking around</i>
<i>the Christmas tree</i> ♪

13:11.332 --> 13:13.585
♪ <i>Let the Christmas</i>
<i>spirit ring...</i> ♪

13:13.668 --> 13:15.879
-Hey.
-Hey.

13:15.962 --> 13:17.380
-Merry Christmas, Miguel.
-Hey.

13:17.464 --> 13:20.133
Hey, Peggy. Good to see you.
How's it going?

13:20.216 --> 13:21.676
Marshall, take it easy
tonight, okay?

13:21.760 --> 13:23.470
Keep an eye on him.
Good to see you.

13:23.553 --> 13:24.471
-Hey.
-Hey, Jack.

13:24.554 --> 13:25.555
We're over here, man.

13:26.931 --> 13:28.808
Why'd you bring your girlfriend
if you know that she hates me?

13:28.892 --> 13:30.518
She doesn't hate you, she just,
you know, she thinks you're

13:30.602 --> 13:32.645
-a lot. Come on.
-That's the same...
Hi. Hey, Rebecca.

13:32.729 --> 13:34.022
How's it going?

13:34.105 --> 13:37.942
Uh... you have been hogging
my guy.

13:38.026 --> 13:39.694
In fact, he's been
flaking on me so much

13:39.778 --> 13:41.488
to spend time with you that
I started calling him Dandruff.

13:41.571 --> 13:43.365
(Jack and Miguel laugh)

13:43.448 --> 13:46.743
-On account of all the flaking.
-Hilarious.

13:46.826 --> 13:49.120
Hey, Migs, was that a new
El Cam parked out front?

13:49.204 --> 13:50.455
I got to, I got to take
a look at that.

13:50.538 --> 13:51.748
MIGUEL: Oh, yeah,
come on, I'll show you.

13:51.831 --> 13:53.041
You know what, actually,
I'm thinking more of a,

13:53.124 --> 13:55.043
uh, a private viewing.

13:55.126 --> 13:57.170
-No.
-Yeah, no, why don't you,
you stick around?

13:57.253 --> 13:59.964
You guys talk amongst
yourselves.

14:00.048 --> 14:02.175
Get to know each other.

14:02.258 --> 14:04.260
(sighs)

14:05.261 --> 14:07.972
"Amongst"?

14:08.056 --> 14:10.475
-He's never used that word.
-Yeah.

14:10.558 --> 14:12.268
Not exactly subtle, is he?

14:12.352 --> 14:15.063
Like a brick through a window.

14:15.146 --> 14:16.564
Yeah.

14:16.648 --> 14:18.566
Um...

14:21.403 --> 14:23.279
-So...
-So, uh...

14:23.363 --> 14:26.658
Sorry. You-you first.

14:26.741 --> 14:28.159
Why do you say people's names
all the time?

14:28.243 --> 14:30.036
"Peggy!

14:30.120 --> 14:31.746
"Marshall! Jack!

14:31.830 --> 14:33.206
Great to see you, Jack."

14:33.289 --> 14:36.334
Uh, it's...

14:36.418 --> 14:38.586
It's just a little
business trick that I use.

14:38.670 --> 14:41.047
I use it to remember
people's names.

14:41.131 --> 14:42.590
You look someone
right in the eye,

14:42.674 --> 14:46.302
you say their name, Rebecca,
and you...

14:46.386 --> 14:47.804
And does that work?

14:47.887 --> 14:50.765
Yeah, it does.
And most people like it.

14:50.849 --> 14:53.560
Well, Miguel,

14:53.643 --> 14:56.980
I'm not most people, <i>Miguel.</i>

14:57.063 --> 15:00.150
Okay, yeah, now I can see
how that can be annoying.

15:00.233 --> 15:01.443
(chuckles)

15:01.526 --> 15:03.319
("Colours" by Donovan playing)

15:03.403 --> 15:05.280
♪ <i>Yellow is the color</i> ♪

15:05.363 --> 15:07.115
-♪ <i>Of my true love's hair</i> ♪
-(indistinct conversation)

15:07.198 --> 15:10.076
-♪ <i>In the morning</i> ♪
-Just go say hi.

15:10.160 --> 15:12.412
-Watch this.
-♪ <i>When we rise</i> ♪

15:12.495 --> 15:16.833
♪ <i>In the morning when we rise</i> ♪

15:16.916 --> 15:19.210
♪ <i>That's the time...</i> ♪

15:19.294 --> 15:20.962
-Hi.
-Hi.

15:21.046 --> 15:23.006
-Miguel.
-Miguel, I'm Shelly.

15:23.089 --> 15:24.674
-Nice to meet you, Shelly.
-Nice to meet you.

15:26.051 --> 15:28.219
(laughter)

15:28.303 --> 15:30.597
♪ ♪

15:32.140 --> 15:34.059
Hi.

15:34.142 --> 15:36.936
♪ ♪

15:37.020 --> 15:38.313
Oh, my God...

15:38.396 --> 15:42.359
♪ <i>Freedom is a word</i>
<i>I rarely use</i> ♪

15:42.442 --> 15:45.528
♪ <i>Without thinking</i> ♪

15:45.612 --> 15:47.322
♪ <i>Mm-hmm</i> ♪

15:47.405 --> 15:49.282
♪ <i>Without thinking</i> ♪

15:49.366 --> 15:52.118
-♪ <i>Mm-hmm...</i> ♪
-Welcome home, buddy.

15:52.202 --> 15:53.119
What do you want
from me, Shelly?

15:53.203 --> 15:54.162
I made it home for dinner

15:54.245 --> 15:55.747
-just like you asked me to.
-Oh, gee.

15:55.830 --> 15:57.582
I guess I should have scheduled
Andy's parent-teacher conference

15:57.665 --> 15:59.626
<i>-during dinner, then, but...</i>
<i>-That's just ridiculous.</i>

15:59.709 --> 16:01.044
<i>SHELLY:</i>
<i>Did you know Rebecca told me</i>
<i>Jack gets home...</i>

16:01.127 --> 16:02.504
<i>-MIGUEL: Oh, no, no, no.</i>
<i>-No, every single night at 6:00.</i>

16:02.587 --> 16:03.713
<i>MIGUEL: No, we're not having</i>
<i>this conversation.</i>

16:03.797 --> 16:04.923
<i>-SHELLY: Every night...</i>
<i>-I am not Jack!</i>

16:05.006 --> 16:07.717
<i>SHELLY:</i>
<i>You certainly are not.</i>

16:17.060 --> 16:18.937
♪ ♪

16:35.912 --> 16:38.498
Rebecca?

16:38.581 --> 16:39.874
Becca?

16:45.171 --> 16:46.673
Rebecca.

16:46.756 --> 16:48.383
(Rebecca laughs nearby)

16:56.391 --> 16:58.435
-(humming happily)
-Rebecca?

16:58.518 --> 17:01.271
-Honey?
-Miguel!

17:01.354 --> 17:03.732
Oh, it's snowing.

17:03.815 --> 17:06.901
It's so beautiful.

17:06.985 --> 17:10.447
-Yes.
-Come dance with me.

17:10.530 --> 17:12.699
It's beautiful
and it's cold, honey.

17:12.782 --> 17:13.950
(humming)

17:14.034 --> 17:17.078
You're not wearing a coat.

17:17.162 --> 17:18.163
Aw, geez.

17:19.873 --> 17:21.332
(grunts)

17:21.416 --> 17:23.877
Here, honey, put this on.

17:23.960 --> 17:25.628
We got to get you warm.
All right?

17:25.712 --> 17:27.547
Come on, let's get back
in the house.

17:27.630 --> 17:29.257
We'll dance in the house, okay?

17:29.341 --> 17:31.092
Oh... oh!

17:31.176 --> 17:32.552
(laughing)

17:32.635 --> 17:35.013
See, isn't this so much fun?

17:35.096 --> 17:37.599
-(groaning)
-(Rebecca laughing)

17:39.976 --> 17:42.228
-No more fun, honey.
-(humming)

17:42.312 --> 17:43.730
We've got to get inside, okay?

17:43.813 --> 17:46.691
(pained groan)

18:02.207 --> 18:04.209
♪ ♪

18:07.629 --> 18:09.839
Jack died.

18:15.470 --> 18:17.931
<i>REBECCA:</i>
<i>These past few years, Miguel,</i>

18:18.014 --> 18:21.643
<i>you've been so good to me,</i>
<i>to us.</i>

18:21.726 --> 18:24.854
And I just think

18:24.938 --> 18:27.107
somewhere along the way I...

18:27.190 --> 18:30.694
I'm moving to Houston.

18:30.777 --> 18:34.656
<i>I got, I got a job offer there</i>
<i>a few months back.</i>

18:34.739 --> 18:37.033
It's-it's near my kids.

18:38.493 --> 18:41.871
<i>It's just, I don't,</i>
<i>I don't know what else to do.</i>

18:41.955 --> 18:44.374
<i>You're my favorite person.</i>

18:48.461 --> 18:51.798
<i>MIGUEL:</i>
<i>Hey, Andy. So, I'm</i>
<i>officially in Houston.</i>

18:51.881 --> 18:55.635
I have box seats
for next week's game, so...

18:55.719 --> 18:57.595
I was just calling
to make sure

18:57.679 --> 18:59.806
you got my last message.
I, uh...

18:59.889 --> 19:02.225
I wanted to see if you were
free this weekend.

19:02.308 --> 19:04.310
So give your dad a call back.

19:07.522 --> 19:11.651
(phone ringing)

19:11.735 --> 19:15.989
Hello? Oh, hey, Mami.
I was...

19:16.072 --> 19:17.782
What's wrong?

19:22.412 --> 19:23.955
(laughter)

19:24.039 --> 19:26.041
(indistinct chatter)

19:41.014 --> 19:42.557
(kids laughing)

19:45.477 --> 19:48.188
(woman speaking Spanish)

19:48.271 --> 19:52.275
<i>Mira,</i> it's the cowboy!
(laughs)

19:52.359 --> 19:55.570
Hide your cattle.
(speaks Spanish)

19:55.653 --> 19:56.613
-Hi.
-Mmm.

19:56.696 --> 19:58.031
(laughter)

19:58.114 --> 20:00.867
Look at him. He looks
like a Taíno Gordon Gekko.

20:00.950 --> 20:02.869
<i>Sí. ¡Gordo Geco!</i>

20:02.952 --> 20:04.579
(laughter)

20:04.662 --> 20:06.456
(speaking Spanish)

20:27.394 --> 20:29.354
♪ ♪

20:32.982 --> 20:35.026
BEATRIZ:
<i>Mijo.</i>

20:38.363 --> 20:40.365
He died proud of you.

20:41.908 --> 20:43.827
-He'd want you to know that.
-Yeah.

20:43.910 --> 20:47.747
I just wish I would have had
more time with him.

20:47.831 --> 20:50.875
I know, <i>papá,</i> I know.

20:52.002 --> 20:53.920
Whew.

20:56.548 --> 20:59.300
<i>Ven,</i> come help me with Gabi.

20:59.384 --> 21:01.136
Okay.

21:03.722 --> 21:06.391
(speaking Spanish)

21:26.536 --> 21:29.039
Okay. Come on, <i>papi.</i>

21:34.377 --> 21:36.379
I cannot believe

21:36.463 --> 21:39.799
Gabi is still holding on. Wow.

21:39.883 --> 21:42.177
I don't know how
you do it, Mami.

21:44.429 --> 21:47.974
I hated Gabi growing up.
Hated her.

21:48.058 --> 21:50.685
-What?
-We fought over everything.

21:50.769 --> 21:52.896
Our parents, clothes, boys.

21:55.857 --> 21:59.486
She used to get
these terrible headaches.

21:59.569 --> 22:02.155
I was convinced she was
faking it for attention.

22:02.238 --> 22:03.907
Had to be.

22:06.576 --> 22:10.622
24 years old, massive stroke.

22:12.457 --> 22:15.043
She wasn't faking.

22:18.463 --> 22:20.131
I see how hard you work.

22:22.592 --> 22:27.013
-Thankless work.
-There is no thankless.

22:27.097 --> 22:29.974
Love is giving your heart
without expectation.

22:30.058 --> 22:33.853
(scoffs)
Well...

22:33.937 --> 22:36.398
I don't know that
I have that in me.

22:36.481 --> 22:39.109
And right now

22:39.192 --> 22:42.237
I'm just, um...

22:42.320 --> 22:45.281
I don't know, I'm just
a little lost right now.

22:45.365 --> 22:46.658
<i>Mira.</i>

22:48.576 --> 22:51.955
I know you will find your way.

22:52.038 --> 22:53.540
I know you will, <i>mijo.</i>

22:55.041 --> 22:58.128
I also know you'll find someone
to love like that again.

23:07.345 --> 23:11.641
Well, you know,
I think my biggest regret

23:11.725 --> 23:14.477
is probably not getting
Papi's coquito recipe.

23:14.561 --> 23:16.855
(scoffs) <i>Coño,</i>
who do you think taught him?

23:16.938 --> 23:19.524
-Prove it.
-(both laugh)

23:19.607 --> 23:22.110
(exclaims in Spanish)

23:51.931 --> 23:53.933
♪ ♪

24:15.705 --> 24:17.248
(computer chimes)

24:33.056 --> 24:33.973
RANDALL:
Oh, gobble-gobble, party people!

24:34.057 --> 24:35.517
Gobble-gobble.

24:35.600 --> 24:37.811
KEVIN: Gobble-go-- I-I'm not
doing that. Get in here.

24:37.894 --> 24:38.895
-KATE: Come on.
-(Randall laughs)

24:38.978 --> 24:40.063
-Hey.
-Hey.

24:40.146 --> 24:41.940
-Happy Thanksgiving Eve.
-Happy Thanksgiving.

24:42.023 --> 24:43.149
-Hey.
-What's up, man?

24:43.233 --> 24:44.275
KATE: Wait,
where's Beth and the girls?

24:44.359 --> 24:45.568
RANDALL:
Coming up tomorrow.

24:45.652 --> 24:47.612
Uh, where are my adorable
nieces and nephews?

24:47.696 --> 24:49.072
Oh, you just missed them.

24:49.155 --> 24:50.448
-Philip took 'em on
a nature walk.
-Yeah.

24:50.532 --> 24:52.784
A Brit, his stepkids,
and a TV star's twins.

24:52.867 --> 24:54.327
I pitched it to my agents,
and they were like,

24:54.411 --> 24:56.371
-"Too hard to follow."
-I wonder why.

24:56.454 --> 24:58.581
Hey, Ma. It's Randall.

24:58.665 --> 25:01.876
Mm, my son. My son.

25:01.960 --> 25:05.088
It's good to see you.

25:05.171 --> 25:06.089
Miguelón.

25:06.172 --> 25:07.340
-Randall.
-My guy.

25:07.424 --> 25:09.050
-(groans)
-What? Oh.

25:09.134 --> 25:10.885
-You okay there?
-Yeah, I'm okay.

25:10.969 --> 25:12.637
I-I think I just slept
on my back wrong.

25:12.721 --> 25:14.848
In fact, I'm gonna go get
some Tylenol.

25:14.931 --> 25:17.142
-Are you gonna be okay, honey?
-Mm-hmm.

25:17.225 --> 25:19.102
Okay, great, I'll be right back.

25:19.185 --> 25:20.478
Right on, man.

25:22.355 --> 25:23.982
You look good, Ma.

25:24.065 --> 25:27.318
-You feeling okay?
-I'm hanging in there.

25:27.402 --> 25:28.695
Hanging in there.
What are you talking about?

25:28.778 --> 25:30.238
You're doing better than that.

25:30.321 --> 25:31.740
Randall, she was this close
to going on that nature walk.

25:31.823 --> 25:34.367
Yeah, she was.

25:34.451 --> 25:36.494
Where is Miguel?

25:36.578 --> 25:38.580
-Where did Miguel go?
-He, uh...

25:38.663 --> 25:41.207
Miguel? Miguel!

25:41.291 --> 25:42.375
-Mom...
-Mom, it's all right.
-Miguel?

25:42.459 --> 25:44.836
-It's all right.
-He's gonna be right back.

25:44.919 --> 25:47.922
Everything's all right.
It's okay. Hey, look at me.

25:48.006 --> 25:48.965
Everything is all right.

25:49.049 --> 25:50.842
-M-Miguel...
-Everything is all right.

25:50.925 --> 25:52.761
It's okay, I'm right here.

25:52.844 --> 25:55.430
-I'm sorry.
-Oh, Miguel.

25:55.513 --> 25:57.682
I thought you...

25:57.766 --> 25:59.142
I won't leave you.

25:59.225 --> 26:02.395
I'm sorry.
I won't leave you again.

26:07.442 --> 26:09.444
♪ ♪

26:12.739 --> 26:14.449
Ha! Liar.

26:15.450 --> 26:17.535
(chimes)

26:17.619 --> 26:20.413
(chuckles) Shoot. Um...

26:20.497 --> 26:22.499
(typing)

26:26.544 --> 26:28.088
(Rebecca laughs)

26:28.171 --> 26:30.465
(sighs)

26:31.508 --> 26:34.344
Hey, Bob. (sighs)
I hate to do this to you, man,

26:34.427 --> 26:36.262
but we've got a small fire
we need to put out here.

26:37.889 --> 26:40.850
-(line rings)
<i>-REBECCA: Hi.</i>
<i>Okay, okay, so, um...</i>

26:40.934 --> 26:43.353
<i>-So, I'm running in</i>
<i>for one item...</i>
-Mm-hmm.

26:43.436 --> 26:44.854
<i>...and I head for the express.</i>

26:44.938 --> 26:47.107
<i>And I'm just about to put</i>
<i>my item on the counter,</i>

26:47.190 --> 26:48.775
<i>no purse.</i>

26:48.858 --> 26:50.985
<i>-No purse, keys...</i>
-(laughs)

26:51.069 --> 26:52.946
What ever happened to, um,
to what's-his-name?

26:53.029 --> 26:55.573
<i>Was a nice guy, kind of boring.</i>

26:55.657 --> 26:57.409
<i>Um... Matt.</i>

26:57.492 --> 26:59.369
You are awful. (laughs)

26:59.452 --> 27:02.997
-(chuckles)
<i>-We dated for</i>
<i>a few more months, and...</i>

27:04.332 --> 27:07.502
Oh, hell, he was boring.
It was boring.

27:07.585 --> 27:08.920
(chuckles) See?

27:09.004 --> 27:10.380
<i>-(laughing)</i>
-(sighs)

27:10.463 --> 27:12.132
Um... I'm gonna be out

27:12.215 --> 27:14.259
in your neck of the woods
next week.

27:14.342 --> 27:16.428
<i>For business.</i>

27:16.511 --> 27:18.013
<i>-Really?</i>
-Yeah.

27:18.096 --> 27:20.890
Should we meet up for dinner?

27:25.937 --> 27:27.981
Oh, I see him.
Thank you so much.

27:30.734 --> 27:32.736
It's so good to see you.
Wow. You look great.

27:32.819 --> 27:34.571
Thank you. You, too.

27:34.654 --> 27:37.157
-Oh, thank you.
-Oh, goodness. You barely age.

27:37.240 --> 27:38.992
Oh, you should talk.
Look at you.

27:39.075 --> 27:40.994
-Wow. Here.
-(chuckles)

27:42.495 --> 27:44.622
-Thanks.
-Mm-hmm.

27:44.706 --> 27:46.291
(sighs)

27:48.209 --> 27:50.337
-Okay.
-(sighs)

27:52.047 --> 27:53.214
(Miguel sighs)

27:53.298 --> 27:55.300
-So...
-So... Uh, you go.

27:55.383 --> 27:56.509
(laughs)

27:56.593 --> 27:59.596
Uh, how long are you in town?

27:59.679 --> 28:02.891
Uh, just a few days. You?

28:02.974 --> 28:05.101
Interesting. You're--
You live here.

28:05.185 --> 28:06.686
-Obviously. I don't know
why I said that.
-I do.

28:06.770 --> 28:08.480
(laughs)

28:08.563 --> 28:09.939
That was a dumb thing to say.

28:10.023 --> 28:12.692
Um... I'm just...

28:12.776 --> 28:15.028
It's-- Uh...

28:16.071 --> 28:17.822
It's really nice to see you.

28:17.906 --> 28:19.741
(chuckles)

28:21.034 --> 28:23.328
Rebecca, um...

28:25.038 --> 28:27.665
I spent the last eight years
wondering

28:27.749 --> 28:29.834
if I made the right decision.

28:31.252 --> 28:34.881
I have replayed it over
and over in my head,

28:34.964 --> 28:36.591
and, um...

28:38.343 --> 28:39.844
I had to leave.

28:40.887 --> 28:44.349
I never felt like I belonged.

28:45.850 --> 28:50.063
Puerto Rican or American.
Spanish or English.

28:50.146 --> 28:52.190
I've just...

28:52.273 --> 28:55.819
I've never felt at home
anywhere.

28:57.904 --> 29:00.490
And if I'm being honest,

29:00.573 --> 29:04.911
the first time that
I ever felt homesick in my life

29:04.994 --> 29:07.789
was when I left you
on that porch.

29:10.000 --> 29:12.002
And I'm not really...

29:12.085 --> 29:15.130
sure how to explain it.

29:20.927 --> 29:22.971
It's really nice to see you,
too.

29:23.054 --> 29:25.056
♪ ♪

29:39.320 --> 29:40.947
(Rebecca laughs)

29:41.031 --> 29:42.449
(both chuckle)

29:42.532 --> 29:44.492
REBECCA:
Hmm.

29:45.785 --> 29:48.163
You should have your company
open up a branch

29:48.246 --> 29:49.831
-here in Pittsburgh.
-(laughs)

29:49.914 --> 29:53.335
Okay. Uh, well,
it would save on airfare.

29:53.418 --> 29:55.503
-Uh-huh.
-I could put a down payment
on a house

29:55.587 --> 29:57.589
with what I've spent on flights
these past few months.

29:57.672 --> 29:59.507
-(Rebecca whimpers)
-Actually,

29:59.591 --> 30:01.843
I have been discussing
retirement packages

30:01.926 --> 30:03.553
-with my partners.
-What? (gasps)

30:03.636 --> 30:04.763
Retire.

30:04.846 --> 30:07.140
-Yeah?
-Come on. Retire and come here.

30:07.223 --> 30:09.642
Be here. Please.

30:10.894 --> 30:13.646
Mmm... Mmm.

30:17.984 --> 30:19.778
(Rebecca sighs)

30:29.162 --> 30:30.914
We never talk about him.

30:38.213 --> 30:41.424
Sometimes I wonder
what he'd think about all this.

30:42.509 --> 30:45.720
I've wondered, too. Obviously.

30:45.804 --> 30:49.474
But, I mean,
the amount of time I've spent...

30:49.557 --> 30:52.394
wondering about all of this...

30:56.856 --> 30:58.066
And?

31:01.653 --> 31:04.989
I think he would want
what's best for us.

31:06.449 --> 31:08.410
For both of us.

31:09.786 --> 31:13.832
His two favorite people
he once left alone in a bar

31:13.915 --> 31:15.750
until they became friends.

31:23.842 --> 31:26.177
We have to tell the kids.

31:28.888 --> 31:31.766
Okay. So,
the kids know you'll be here.

31:31.850 --> 31:33.476
And, thankfully,
you're no stranger

31:33.560 --> 31:36.229
-to Pearson Thanksgivings.
-Oh, yeah. I know the drill.

31:36.312 --> 31:37.814
-Uh, Pilgrim Rick.
-Uh-huh.

31:37.897 --> 31:39.774
-Hot dogs and <i>Police Academy 3.</i>
-Yeah.

31:39.858 --> 31:41.776
And we just take it slow.

31:41.860 --> 31:42.986
-Yeah.
-You know,
let them get used to the fact

31:43.069 --> 31:44.654
that you're back
over dinner.

31:44.738 --> 31:46.239
-And then over dessert,
we can wait.
-Mm-hmm.

31:46.322 --> 31:48.533
We can just ease-ease right in.

31:48.616 --> 31:50.827
-Right. Easy.
-Yeah.

31:51.870 --> 31:54.497
-This is gonna be fine.
-Yeah.

31:54.581 --> 31:55.623
No, I think you're pretty fine.

31:55.707 --> 31:58.418
-Oh, you do, do you? Oh.
-I really do.

31:58.501 --> 32:00.462
-Hey, come here for a second.
-Oh. (chuckles)

32:03.173 --> 32:04.466
(door opens)

32:04.549 --> 32:05.842
KEVIN:
Hello, hello.

32:05.925 --> 32:08.136
The hell?

32:09.179 --> 32:10.764
Um...

32:12.557 --> 32:15.769
RANDALL:
I'm sorry,
you two are living together?

32:15.852 --> 32:17.312
How long have you been dating?

32:18.396 --> 32:20.273
After Tess was born,

32:20.357 --> 32:22.150
-we hooked up.
-(groans)

32:22.233 --> 32:23.985
MIGUEL:
Uh, well, what she means
by "hooked up"

32:24.069 --> 32:25.236
is that we, that we met up.

32:25.320 --> 32:26.404
We connected.

32:26.488 --> 32:28.031
-Right, honey? Yeah.
-REBECCA: Yeah.

32:28.114 --> 32:29.616
Wait, what does
the other "hook up" mean?

32:29.699 --> 32:30.742
Slept together.

32:30.825 --> 32:32.369
Oh, no.

32:32.452 --> 32:34.996
No, no. That didn't start
until much more recently.

32:35.080 --> 32:35.997
-(others groaning)
-Oh, no.

32:36.081 --> 32:37.165
Don't need to hear all that.

32:37.248 --> 32:38.667
I don't know why
you guys are so surprised.

32:38.750 --> 32:39.709
I knew it.

32:39.793 --> 32:41.127
-Didn't I say, baby?
-She did.

32:41.211 --> 32:42.796
I mean, I said, "We haven't seen
the last of Migs."

32:42.879 --> 32:44.172
And then I was like,

32:44.255 --> 32:46.758
"Why does your mom have
Fourth of July plans?

32:46.841 --> 32:48.468
Like, she never has
Fourth of July plans."

32:48.551 --> 32:50.970
-No offense, Rebecca.
-None-none taken. (chuckles)

32:53.807 --> 32:56.601
Right, well, I mean...

32:56.685 --> 32:58.061
if you're happy...

32:58.144 --> 33:00.355
-(mouths)
-KEVIN: What the...?

33:00.438 --> 33:01.898
-KATE: What?
-The hell are you two
talking about?

33:01.981 --> 33:03.066
Uh, no, this is...

33:03.149 --> 33:04.317
He was Dad's best friend.

33:04.401 --> 33:05.443
This i--
How do you two justify this?

33:05.527 --> 33:07.737
Kevin, you are an adult.

33:07.821 --> 33:09.447
Act like one.

33:09.531 --> 33:11.991
(stammers) Uh, guys, I...

33:12.075 --> 33:14.411
I loved your father.

33:14.494 --> 33:16.538
I-I loved him so much,

33:16.621 --> 33:18.456
but...

33:18.540 --> 33:21.334
I am in love with your mom now.

33:21.418 --> 33:23.503
A-And we waited a very long time
before...

33:23.586 --> 33:25.213
This whole thing is ridiculous.

33:25.296 --> 33:26.673
This is ridiculous.

33:28.383 --> 33:30.885
Thanksgiving's canceled.

33:30.969 --> 33:32.846
-And I'm taking the hat with me.
-Kevin.

33:32.929 --> 33:35.015
♪ ♪

33:36.433 --> 33:39.185
<i>I love you, Miguel.</i>

33:39.269 --> 33:42.772
<i>I promise to love you</i>
<i>until the end.</i>

33:42.856 --> 33:44.858
<i>(Miguel speaking Spanish)</i>

33:48.737 --> 33:50.697
<i>REBECCA:</i>
<i>I will care for you</i>

33:50.780 --> 33:53.116
<i>until the end of my days,</i>

33:53.199 --> 33:55.410
<i>in sickness and in health.</i>

33:56.411 --> 33:59.122
<i>(Miguel speaking Spanish)</i>

34:03.126 --> 34:05.378
<i>REBECCA:</i>
<i>Until death parts us.</i>

34:07.922 --> 34:10.216
He chased after her in the snow,
and he fell.

34:10.300 --> 34:11.634
He does not want
to talk about it.

34:11.718 --> 34:13.386
I didn't think it was that bad,
but then again

34:13.470 --> 34:15.513
he always puts on a brave face,
so...

34:17.223 --> 34:18.767
Hey.

34:18.850 --> 34:21.353
-What'd I miss?
-Excuse me.

34:26.608 --> 34:29.319
(sighs) We should talk.

34:38.995 --> 34:40.914
Guys, it's-it's just a bruise.
It's fine.

34:40.997 --> 34:42.082
(stammers)
It's embarrassing to...

34:42.165 --> 34:44.042
to even talk about, really.

34:44.125 --> 34:46.211
I think-- We think

34:46.294 --> 34:49.506
-that it's time to get
full-time help for her.
-Yeah.

34:50.757 --> 34:52.300
She has full-time help.

34:52.384 --> 34:54.552
That you dismiss
in the middle of the day.

34:54.636 --> 34:57.263
We're talking about permanent,
around-the-clock care

34:57.347 --> 34:59.849
-to help you more.
-It's not that easy, Randall.

34:59.933 --> 35:01.976
She doesn't respond well
to strangers.

35:02.060 --> 35:04.521
What would you have done if
you had been seriously injured,

35:04.604 --> 35:05.772
-Miguel?
-Well, I wasn't
seriously injured.

35:05.855 --> 35:07.023
But you could have been.

35:07.107 --> 35:08.900
Kevin, she's my wife!

35:11.403 --> 35:12.696
(scoffs)

35:12.779 --> 35:14.030
I made a vow.

35:14.114 --> 35:15.740
We know, Miguel.

35:18.410 --> 35:22.038
I have failed at everything else
in my life.

35:23.832 --> 35:26.918
My parents. Shelly.

35:28.586 --> 35:29.963
(breathes shakily)

35:30.046 --> 35:32.298
I haven't seen my son
in five years.

35:32.382 --> 35:35.176
We are not questioning
how much you love her.

35:35.260 --> 35:37.679
Kate, I am not leaving her side.

35:37.762 --> 35:40.432
Okay? This is...

35:40.515 --> 35:44.060
Every morning at 6:45,

35:44.144 --> 35:47.063
I am the first thing she sees
